'''Cutler's resin''' is a synthetic [[resin]] made of [[pine]] [[Pitch (resin)|pitch]], [[beeswax]], and [[sawdust]] or [[carnauba wax]] used for [[centuries]] (to today) to attach [[knife]] handles. It is used as both an [[adhesive]] and for [[waterproofing]]. The word cutler means "one who makes knives", hence the word "cutlery".

