{{one source|date=May 2014}}{{refimprove|date=May 2012}} {{Infobox prepared food | name = Tastet | image = | caption = | alternate_name = | country = [[Spain]] | region = [[Catalonia]] | creator = | course = [[Hors d'oeuvre]] | type = | served = | main_ingredient = | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Tastet''' is a word of [[Catalan language|Catalan]] origin meaning 'a small taste of food'. The tastet is a variation of the [[tapas]] serving style; larger and more complex than tapas but smaller than a plate. Emphasis is placed on taste and presentation. The tastet can be served as an appetizer or as a small collection for a complete meal. The tastet serving style allows for the appreciation of several flavours within a single meal.{{citation needed|date=May 2012}}
Restaurants may favour the tastet as a specialised menu format, and may offer all their tastets at a uniform price. One such restaurant is "El Jardi Del Tastets" in [[Palamos]], [[Spain]]. <ref> [http://www.eljardidelstastets.com] El Jardi Dels Tastets</ref>
